text.tspan: Protein supply from animal foods vs. GDP per capita, 1990
Protein supply is measured in grams per person per day, and includes protein from meat, dairy, eggs and
seafood. Gross domestic product per capita is adjusted for inflation and cross-country price differences.
Data source: Food and Agriculture Organization of the United Nations (2023); World Bank (2023)
